message.entry: Error occurred while trying to clear cells.
Range input must specified as a character vector or a 4 element vector specifying [startRow, startCol, numRows, numCols].
Range input exceeds bounds for this file extension. Row values must be between 1 and {0,number,integer} and columns values must be between ''A'' and ''{1}''.
Unable to determine range. Range must be a named range in the sheet or a single cell within ''{0}{1,number,integer}''.
Unable to find named range ''{0}'' in the sheet.
Unable to determine range. Range must be of the form ''A1'' (cell), ''A:B'' (column-select), ''1:5'' (row-select), ''A1:B5'' (rectangle-select), or a valid named range in the sheet.
Data must be one or two dimensions.
The ''types'' input to the read method must be a 2 dimensional matrix of the same size as the range and must be of class uint8.
Data exceeds sheet bounds. Consider using the XLSX extension or splitting the data across multiple sheets or files.
Range input must be a string scalar, character vector or numeric array.

A numeric range must be 1, 2, or 4 positive integers of the form:
 [start-row, start-column, end-row, end-column], where end>=start or
 [start-row, start-column] or 
 [start-row].
Error writing to sheet. The range or sheet is protected, the data is too large for a cell, or the workbook is marked as final.
The specified file exists and contains an active unsupported filter. To write to the file, clear all active filters.
Text type must be either ''char'' or ''string''.
Supplying ''NumHeaderLines'' with ''Range'' or ''DataRange'' is only supported when the range value is of the form ''A:B'' (column-select).
Encountered an internal error.
Encountered an internal error: ''{0}''
Range specified does not contain any cells with data.
Merged rows found in sheet ''{0}''. Set ''MergedCellRowRule'' to any value other than 'error' to parse sheets with merged rows.
Merged columns found in sheet ''{0}''. Set ''MergedCellColumnRule'' to any value other than 'error' to parse sheets with merged columns.
Supplying ''MergedCellColumnRule'' and ''MergedCellRowRule'' is only supported in ''UseExcel'' false mode.
